sue |\n|----------|-------|\n| `apps/cli/src/acp/ACPAdapter.ts` + `acp/types.ts` | The ACP protocol layer heavily uses `AutonomyMode` as an API type. This is an external-facing protocol boundary. |\n| `apps/cli/src/exec/renderlessExecRunner.tsx` + `exec/types.ts` | The renderless exec flow uses `AutonomyMode` throughout as primary truth. |\n| `packages/component-library/src/chat/AutonomyModeSwitcher/` | The entire UI component operates on `AutonomyMode`. Needs redesign to separate mode from level. |\n| Enterprise controls (`SessionDefaultsSection.module.tsx`, `EnterpriseControlsForm.module.tsx`) | Admin UI for org defaults uses `AutonomyMode` for the session default selector. |\n| `apps/cli/src/agent/autonomy.ts` | `getRequiredAutonomyLevel()` returns `AutonomyMode` where it should return `AutonomyLevel`. |\n\n### Priority 3 -- Cleanup needed\n\n| Location | Issue |\n|----------|-------|\n| CLI hooks (`useAgent.ts`, `useToolExecution.ts`, `CompactionManager.ts`) | Many `getCurrentAutonomyMode()` calls that should use decoupled fields |\n| `apps/cli/src/services/hook-utils.ts` | `convertAutonomyModeToPermissionMode()` needs a version taking new types |\n| `packages/component-library/src/chat/ModelSwitcher/` | Uses `currentAutonomyMode === AutonomyMode.Spec` instead of `interactionMode` |\n| E2E test fixtures (11 files) | Settings JSON files only have `autonomyMode`, no decoupled fields |\n| `docs/examples/creating-session-settings-property-end-to-end.md` | Should show new pattern |\n\n---\n\n## Issue Summary\n\n| # | Severity | Category | Description |\n|---|----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | **Medium** | Migration gap | Backend webhooks (Slack/Linear) create sessions with only legacy `autonomyMode`, missing decoupled fields |\n| 2 | **Medium** | Migration gap | ACP protocol layer, renderless exec runner, and AutonomyModeSwitcher component still use `AutonomyMode` as primary truth (~35-40 files unmigrated) |\n| 3 | **Medium** | Code quality | Duplicated reso