onomyMode` for the org-level default selector. This is the admin settings UI, not the session connection. The stored value flows through `useSessionDefaultSettings` which normalizes it correctly. Migrating this UI is a separate concern and would require a UX decision (should admins see separate mode + level, or keep the combined selector?).\n\n**Recommendation:** Track as follow-up, not in this PR.\n\n## 2. Refine: Extract Duplicated Resolve+Store Pattern\n\nThe same ~20 lines of \"resolve interaction settings, store to session, derive legacy mode\" logic is copy-pasted **3 times** in the frontend:\n\n1. `SessionStateManager.handleNotification` (line 846)\n2. `SessionStateManager.updateSessionSettings` (line 1136)\n3. `DaemonSessionController.loadSession` (line 1264)\n\nAll three do: `hasDecoupledAutonomyFields` check -> `resolveInteractionSettings()` -> `store.setInteractionMode()` -> `store.setAutonomyLevel()` -> conditional `deriveAutonomyMode` vs raw `autonomyMode` -> `store.setAutonomyMode()`.\n\n**Change:** Extract a private method on `SessionStateManager`:\n\n```ts\nprivate applyInteractionSettings(\n  store: SessionStore,\n  settings: { interactionMode?: DroidInteractionMode; autonomyLevel?: AutonomyLevel; autonomyMode?: AutonomyMode }\n): void {\n  // ... the resolve+store+derive pattern, once\n}\n```\n\nThen have `handleNotification`, `updateSessionSettings`, and `DaemonSessionController.loadSession` (via `sessionManager.applyInteractionSettings(...)`) all call it. This reduces 3x ~20 lines to 1x ~20 lines + 3x 1-line calls.\n\nSimilarly, on the CLI side, `streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` has the `hasDecoupledAutonomyFields` pattern in 2 places (initialize + settings update), and `SessionController.applySettings` has its own version. These are slightly different (CLI uses `setInteractionMode`/`setAutonomyLevel`/`setAutonomyMode` methods rather than store setters), but the `applySettings` method on `SessionController` already serves as the single entry point. The exec runner's two occurrences could call `SessionController.applySettings` instead of inlining the logic -- but this is lower priority since the CLI patterns are simpler (just conditional method calls, no resolve step).\n\n## 3. PR Strategy\n\n### Current state of the PR\n- **Commit 1** (`refactor(monorepo): migrate session settings to decoupled autonomy fields`): The bulk migration -- schemas, CLI, daemon, frontend hooks, state management, UI wiring. 1400+ lines.\n- **Commit 2** (`refactor(frontend): simplify decoupled cloud session defaults`): Small follow-up cleanup.\n- **Commit 3** (`fix(cli): centralize permission outcome handling`): The permission double-processing bug fix.\n\n### Recommendation: Keep as one PR, but reorder commits\n\nBreaking this into multiple PRs has a significant downside: the schema changes in commit 1 add optional fields that **must** be handled consistently across CLI, daemon, and frontend. Shipping the schema change without all consumers updated creates a window where behavior is inconsistent. The permission fix in commit 3 is logically independent but small enough that separating it adds review overhead without real benefit.\n\n**Proposed approach:**\n1. **Keep as one PR** -- the changes are interdependent and the risk of inconsistency across incremental PRs outweighs the review cost.\n2. **Add one small commit** for the refinements above:\n   - Extract `applyInteractionSettings` helper on `SessionStateManager` (dedup 3 sites)\n   - Add `currentInteractionMode` prop to `ModelSwitcher` (consistency)\n   - Add `@deprecated` annotation to `AutonomyModeSwitcher` noting V1.0-only status\n3. Optionally **reorder** so the permission fix commit comes first (it's the most self-contained behavioral fix and easiest to review independently), followed by the migration refactor.\n\n### What NOT to do in this PR (follow-up backlog)\n- Migrate `AutonomyModeSwitcher` component (dies with V1.0 input)\n- Migrate enterprise controls UI (needs UX decision)\n- Migrate CLI-only surfaces: ACP adapter, renderless exec runner, `agent/autonomy.ts`, hooks (`useAgent`, `useToolExecution`) -- these are CLI-internal and don't affect the frontend-daemon connection\n- Migrate backend webhooks (Slack/Linear route handlers)\n\n## Summary of Proposed Changes\n\n| Change | Files | LOC (est) | Priority |\n|--------|-------|-----------|----------|\n| Extract `applyInteractionSettings` on `SessionStateManager` | `SessionStateManager.ts`, `DaemonSessionController.ts` | -40 net | High |\n| Add `currentInteractionMode` to `ModelSwitcher` | `ModelSwitcher/types.ts`, `ModelSwitcher.tsx`, `DroidSessionChat.tsx`, `ChatComposer/types.ts` | +10 | Medium |\n| `@deprecated` annotation on `AutonomyModeSwitcher` | `AutonomyModeSwitcher.tsx` | +2 | Low |\n| (Optional) Reorder commits: permission fix first | git rebase | 0 | Low |\n",
