            "content": "# PR #10048 Review (Round 2) — Post-Deprecation\n\n## Introduction\n\nThis is a second-pass review after the latest two commits that fully removed legacy `autonomyMode` from the frontend and component-library packages, and migrated enterprise controls from `AutonomyMode` to `AutonomyLevel`. The PR now spans 67 files across 10 packages.\n\nThe review was conducted by 4 parallel workers:\n- **CLI + daemon-core** (20 files)\n- **Frontend state + hooks + modules** (28 files)\n- **Component-library + schemas + SDK** (17 files)\n- **Cross-cutting design + completeness audit**\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\nThe PR replaces a combined `AutonomyMode` enum (`normal`, `auto-low`, `auto-high`, `spec`, etc.) with two orthogonal axes:\n\n```\nAutonomyMode (legacy, combined)     →    DroidInteractionMode (Auto | Spec | AGI)\n                                    +    AutonomyLevel (Off | Low | Medium | High)\n```\n\nData flows through: **daemon** (pass-through) → **SessionStateManager** (resolves + stores) → **SessionStore** → **hooks** → **components**. The single resolution utility `resolveInteractionSettings` is used at 10+ call-sites with no duplication.\n\nThe permission flow was also refactored: `processConfirmationOutcome` moved out of `JsonRpcProtocolAdapter` into `PermissionRequestHandler`, establishing a single owner for business logic.\n\n---\n\n## Issue Summary\n\n| # | Severity | Area | Issue |\n|---|----------|------|-------|\n| C1 | Critical | Schemas | `SessionSettingsSchema.autonomyLevel` field rename breaks cross-version compat (old daemon sends `AutonomyMode` value, new client expects `AutonomyLevel`) |\n| M1 | Medium | CLI | `ProceedAutoRun*` and `ProceedOnce` paths still use deprecated `setAutonomyMode()` — inconsistent with `ProceedAlways` migration |\n| M2 | Medium | Component-lib | Missing error handling in V1.1 `onLevelChange`/`onSpecModeChange` callbacks (old code had try/catch) |\n| M3 | Medium | Frontend | Inconsistent default `autonomyLevel`: `SessionDetail.page.tsx` uses `Low`, everywhere else uses `Off` |\n| M4 | Medium | Frontend | Dead `autonomyMode` passthrough in `ActiveSession.module.tsx` — passed to hook but never consumed |\n| M5 | Medium | Frontend | `useActiveSessionSettings` ignores `autonomyMode` from `initialSettings`, creating misleading dead code path |\n| M6 | Medium | CLI | `SessionSettings.interactionMode`/`autonomyLevel` typed as optional but always populated at runtime |\n| M7 | Medium | CLI | `outcome` field optional in `AgentEventPayloads[PermissionResponse]` but always provided |\n| M8 | Medium | Cross-cutting | `SessionDefaultSettingsSchema` not migrated — enterprise controls must use translation utilities |\n| M9 | Medium | Git | Duplicate commits in history (14 commits, ~7 are duplicates from merge/rebase cycle) |\n| M10 | Medium | Component-lib | New `DroidSessionChat` tests are superficial — only check render, not behavioral correctness |\n| L1 | Low | CLI | Naming confusion: `getRequiredAutonomyLevel()` returns `AutonomyMode` |\n| L2 | Low | CLI | Three near-identical state-diff-then-emit blocks in SessionController |\n| L3 | Low | CLI | Test helper reimplements `deriveAutonomyMode` instead of importing it |\n| L4 | Low | Frontend | `resolveInteractionSettings` recomputed on every render in `useActiveSessionSettings` |\n| L5 | Low | Frontend | `disableShiftTabForAutonomyMode` preference now orphaned/dead UI |\n\n---\n\n## Critical Issue Detail\n\n### C1: Schema backward compatibility — `autonomyLevel` field type change\n\n**Files**: `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/client.ts`, `cli.ts`\n\nThe old `SessionSettingsSchema` had a required field `autonomyLevel: z.nativeEnum(AutonomyMode)`. The new schema has `autonomyLevel: z.nativeEnum(AutonomyLevel).optional()` -- a different enum. An old daemon responding with `autonomyLevel: 'normal'` (valid `AutonomyMode`) will fail Zod validation because `'normal'` is not a valid `AutonomyLevel` value (`off|low|medium|