m local variables. The logic is simple (switch on interactionMode + autonomyLevel). **Not a real problem -- the test helper is tightly coupled to the test's mock state by design.**\n\n## L4: `resolveInteractionSettings` recomputed on every render\n**REAL but negligible.** Line 85: `resolveInteractionSettings(...)` called outside `useState` initializer, so it runs on every render but the result is only used once. `useState` ignores subsequent calls. The function is a pure, cheap computation (no allocations beyond a small object). **Technically wasteful, practically zero impact.**\n\n## L5: `disableShiftTabForAutonomyMode` preference now orphaned\n**REAL.** The preference exists at:\n- `app/preferences/types.ts:4` — type definition\n- `app/preferences/keyboardShortcutPreferencesAtom.ts:8` — default value\n- `features/settings/components/PreferencesSection.module.tsx:39-41` — UI toggle\n\nThe keyboard shortcut cycling through autonomy modes was part of `AutonomyModeSwitcher` (now deleted). The `ActiveSession.module.tsx` no longer passes `disableAutonomyModeKeyboardShortcut` prop. The preference toggle in settings is now dead UI -- it controls nothing. **Real, but cosmetic/cleanup.**\n",
